This paper deals with the development of scientometric indicators and methods for evaluative purposes, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as scientometrics is closely related to the management and analysis of digital information. The paper also discusses the measurement of research impact, which is a topic that falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper touches on the use of metrics in research assessment, which is a topic that falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
